### About Dataset

From : https://www.kaggle.com/carrie1/ecommerce-data & https://towardsdatascience.com/@admond1994


The UCI Machine Learning Repository has made this dataset containing actual transactions from 2010 and 2011. The dataset is maintained on their site, where it can be found by the title "Online Retail".

"This is a transnational data set which contains all the transactions occurring between 01/12/2010 and 09/12/2011 for a UK-based and registered non-store online retail.The company mainly sells unique all-occasion gifts. Many customers of the company are wholesalers."

Analyses for this dataset could include time series, clustering, classification and more.

### Patterns of Orders

# Number of invoice group by Month
# Display with Frequency bar chart

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
monthly_sale = df_new.groupby(['InvoiceNo'])['yearMonth'].unique()
monthly_sale.value_counts().sort_index().plot(kind='bar', color='red')
plt.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=1, alpha=0.5)
plt.title('Frequency of Order by Month', fontsize = 12)
plt.xlabel('By month')
plt.ylabel("Orders")
plt.show()

# Display number invoice group by day using set_xticklabels

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
daily_sale = df_new.groupby(['InvoiceNo'])['day'].unique()
ax = daily_sale.value_counts().sort_index().plot(kind='bar', color='red')
ax.set_xticklabels(('Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thur', 'Fir', 'Sun'), rotation = 'horizontal', fontsize= 14)
plt.title('Frequency of Order by Day', fontsize = 12)
plt.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=1, alpha=0.5)
plt.show()
There is no transaction on Saturday

# Display number invoice group by hour

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
hour_sale = df_new.groupby(['InvoiceNo'])['hour'].unique()
#hour_sale.value_counts().sort_index().plot(kind='bar')
(hour_sale.value_counts()).iloc[0:-1].sort_index().plot(kind='bar', color='red')
plt.title('Frequency of Order by Hour', fontsize = 12)
plt.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=1, alpha=0.5)
plt.show()

# Display Orders by Country

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
country_sale = df_new.groupby(['Country'])['InvoiceNo'].count()
country_sale.sort_index().plot(kind='barh', color='red')
plt.title('Frequency of Order by Day', fontsize = 12)
plt.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=1, alpha=0.5)
plt.show()
